# Deployment & Environment

## Git → GitHub → Netlify Pipeline
- Repo: `github.com/jordanmok88/Evair-H5` (branch: `main`)
- Netlify site: `evair-h5.netlify.app`
- Auto-deploys on push to `main` (GitHub integration)
- An `autopush.sh` script runs locally to auto-commit and push changes periodically
- Git remote uses HTTPS (not SSH). Credentials stored via `git credential.helper store`.

## Netlify Environment Variables
Set via Netlify dashboard (Site configuration > Environment variables):
- `ESIM_ACCESS_CODE` — ESIMAccess supplier code
- `ESIM_SECRET` — ESIMAccess secret
- `RESEND_API_KEY` — Resend email service key
- `RESEND_FROM` — `EvairSIM <service@evairdigital.com>`

## Netlify Functions
Located in `netlify/functions/`. These are serverless functions:
- `esim-proxy.mjs` — proxies ESIMAccess API calls (keeps credentials server-side)
- `send-esim-email.mjs` — sends eSIM activation emails via Resend

## Build
- `npx vite build` — outputs to `dist/`
- Netlify build command: `npm run build`
- Always run build locally after major changes to catch errors before push

## Logo & Assets
- Logo file: `public/evairsim-logo.png` (white background)
- Email uses `evairsim-logo-v2.png` (same image, different filename to bust CDN cache)
- Company website: `evairdigital.com`
- Support email: `service@evairdigital.com`
